Preheat your oven to 200°C. Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop each half into four long strips then halve widthways. Pop the aubergine pieces onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the @Chinese Five Spice{1/2} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then arrange in a single layer. Roast the aubergine on the top shelf until golden brown and soft, ~{25-30%minutes}, turning halfway through.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}. Trim the @carrot{1} and thinly slice into rounds. Halve the @mangetout{80%g} lengthways. Trim the @spring onion{1} and thinly slice. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a garlic press).

Heat a large #frying pan{} over medium-high heat (no oil!) Once hot, add the @sesame seeds{15%g} and cook, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{1-2%minutes}. Once toasted, transfer to a #small bowl{} and pop your pan back on medium high heat.

Add a drizzle of @oil{} to your frying pan and add the onion and carrot. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and stir fry until they are both nicely softened and golden, ~{6-7%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and and mangetout, stir and cook for ~{1-2%minutes}. Gently separate the @udon noodles{300%g} and add them to the pan as well.

Add the @Szechuan paste{100%g} and @water{50%ml}, bring to the boil and simmer until the mixture is piping hot and the sauce coats the veg and noodles, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add the sesame seeds and stir to combine. Taste and add @salt{} and @pepper{} if you feel it needs it.

Serve the noodles in #bowls{}, top with the roasted aubergine and spring onion sprinkled on top and enjoy!

> Watch the sesame seeds like a hawk as they can burn easily.